PRETORIA - ANC secretary general Gwede Mantashe will address the National Union of Mineworkers Central Committee meeting on Thursday. Leaders will look at ways to make NUM the dominant mining union once again.Job losses and new developments in the sector will also be discussed.The gathering comes two days after it was announced that South Africa is in recession.The union's position in light of Cosatu s decision to call on President Jacob Zuma to step down will also be addressed.eNCA